verbose_text: A nonsynonymous LRRK2 (MIM : 609007) variant that causes Parkinson disease (MIM : 607060) was associated with an odds ratio of 4.76 (95% CI [3.25, 6.96]) that a person would have a parent with Parkinson disease; this estimate is consistent with studies of affected family members.
evidence: LRRK2 (MIM: 609007) variant that causes Parkinson disease
